      "content": "i see, so basically just classic western business attire. what if someone is in a place with really strong traditions, like japan or india? like, if a businessman wears a traditional kimono or a kurta to a high-level international meeting, would that still be considered \"sophisticated\" and \"professional\" under your guide, or is that seen as too \"traditional\" for a global business setting?",
